.TH S9S-BACKUP-CLICKHOUSE 1 "April 2026"

.SH NAME
s9s-backup-clickhouse \- Guide to ClickHouse backup and restore via ClusterControl

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B s9s backup
.RI [OPTION]...

.SH DESCRIPTION
This man page describes how to create and restore \fBClickHouse\fP native
backups using \fBs9s\fP and ClusterControl (cmon).

ClickHouse backup uses the \fIclickhouse-native\fP backup method, which
issues a \fBBACKUP ALL TO Disk('backups', ...)\fP SQL command directly on
the ClickHouse node.  The backup is written to the local filesystem path
configured as the \fBbackups\fP disk in ClickHouse's storage settings
(typically \fI/var/lib/clickhouse/backups/\fP).

.SS Backup Methods
Two method names are available:

.TP
.B clickhouse-native
Full backup.  Every database and table in the cluster is archived.

.TP
.B clickhouse-native-incr
Incremental backup.  Only data changed since the most recently completed
\fIclickhouse-native\fP or \fIclickhouse-native-incr\fP backup is stored.
The parent backup is \fBauto-detected\fP by cmon \(em no parent backup ID
needs to be passed by the caller.

.SS Constraints
.IP \(bu 3
Only local-disk storage is supported (the \fBbackups\fP disk in ClickHouse's
storage configuration).  Cloud-only and controller storage are rejected.
.IP \(bu 3
The backup directory on the record is always set to the configured disk
base path.  Passing \fB--backup-dir\fP has no effect on where ClickHouse
writes the backup.
.IP \(bu 3
Backups are always node-local.  There is no built-in streaming to the
controller.

.\"
.\" FULL BACKUP
.\"
.SH FULL BACKUP

A full backup archives every database and table on the cluster.

.B Step 1 \(em find the cluster ID and a backup node
.nf
s9s cluster --list --long
s9s node    --list --long --cluster-id=1
.fi

.B Step 2 \(em create the full backup
.nf
s9s backup \\
    --create \\
    --cluster-id=1 \\
    --nodes=192.168.1.10 \\
    --backup-method=clickhouse-native \\
    --backup-dir=/var/lib/clickhouse/backups/ \\
    --title="weekly_full_2026_04_21" \\
    --wait
.fi

.B Step 3 \(em list available backups
.nf
s9s backup \\
    --list \\
    --long \\
    --cluster-id=1
.fi

The \fBI\fP column shows \fBF\fP for full backups and \fBI\fP for
incremental backups.  Note the \fBID\fP value \(em you will need it to
restore or to build an incremental backup on top.

.\"
.\" INCREMENTAL BACKUP
.\"
.SH INCREMENTAL BACKUP

An incremental backup stores only data that changed after the most recently
completed ClickHouse backup (full or incremental).  cmon auto-detects the
parent \(em you do \fBnot\fP need to pass a parent backup ID.

.B Create an incremental backup
.nf
s9s backup \\
    --create \\
    --cluster-id=1 \\
    --nodes=192.168.1.10 \\
    --backup-method=clickhouse-native-incr \\
    --backup-dir=/var/lib/clickhouse/backups/ \\
    --title="daily_incr_2026_04_21" \\
    --wait
.fi

cmon scans the backup catalogue for the most recent completed
\fIclickhouse-native\fP or \fIclickhouse-native-incr\fP backup belonging
to the same cluster and passes it as \fBbase_backup\fP to ClickHouse.  The
incremental backup record stores the chain relationship so the UI and
retention logic can trace the full ancestry.

If no completed full backup exists when an incremental backup is requested,
the job fails with:

.nf
No completed ClickHouse backup found to use as base for incremental backup.
.fi

Create a full backup first in that case.

.\"
.\" RESTORE
.\"
.SH RESTORE

Both full and incremental backups are restored with the same \fB--restore\fP
option.  When restoring an incremental backup, ClickHouse automatically
applies the full backup chain (full \(-> incremental \(-> \&...) in the
correct order.

.B Step 1 \(em find the backup ID to restore
.nf
s9s backup \\
    --list \\
    --long \\
    --cluster-id=1
.fi

.B Step 2 \(em restore
.nf
s9s backup \\
    --restore \\
    --cluster-id=1 \\
    --backup-id=7 \\
    --nodes=192.168.1.10 \\
    --wait
.fi

The \fB--nodes\fP option selects the ClickHouse node on which the restore
is performed.  If omitted, cmon picks the first available online node.

After the restore completes, tables contain \fBexactly\fP the data that was
present when the backup was taken.  Any data written after the backup was
created will be gone.

.\"
.\" TYPICAL WORKFLOW
.\"
.SH TYPICAL BACKUP AND RESTORE WORKFLOW

The following shows a complete lifecycle: take a full backup, add data,
take an incremental backup, add more data, and then restore.

.B 1. Full backup
.nf
s9s backup \\
    --create \\
    --cluster-id=1 \\
    --nodes=192.168.1.10 \\
    --backup-method=clickhouse-native \\
    --title=full_monday \\
    --wait
.fi

.B 2. List to confirm and note the backup ID
.nf
s9s backup --list --long --cluster-id=1
.fi

.B 3. Incremental backup (no parent ID needed \(em cmon auto-detects)
.nf
s9s backup \\
    --create \\
    --cluster-id=1 \\
    --nodes=192.168.1.10 \\
    --backup-method=clickhouse-native-incr \\
    --title=incr_tuesday \\
    --wait
.fi

.B 4. Restore the incremental backup (applies full chain automatically)
.nf
s9s backup \\
    --restore \\
    --cluster-id=1 \\
    --backup-id=<INCR_ID> \\
    --nodes=192.168.1.10 \\
    --wait
.fi

After the restore, the database contains exactly the state captured at
step 3 (the incremental snapshot), including all data from step 1 (the
full snapshot that came before it).

.\"
.\" BACKUP METHOD NAMES SUMMARY
.\"
.SH BACKUP METHOD NAMES SUMMARY

.TS
allbox tab(|);
l l l.
Method|Type|Parent auto-detected?
clickhouse-native|Full|n/a
clickhouse-native-incr|Incremental|Yes, by cmon
.TE

.\"
.\" OPTIONS
.\"
.SH RELEVANT OPTIONS

.TP
.B \-\-create
Create a new backup.

.TP
.B \-\-restore
Restore an existing backup.

.TP
.BI \-\-cluster-id= INTEGER
The numerical ID of the ClickHouse cluster.

.TP
.BI \-\-nodes= HOSTLIST
The ClickHouse node to run the backup or restore on (e.g.
\fI192.168.1.10\fP).

.TP
.BI \-\-backup-method= METHOD
Use \fIclickhouse-native\fP for a full backup or
\fIclickhouse-native-incr\fP for an incremental backup.

.TP
.BI \-\-backup-id= INTEGER
The numerical ID of the backup to restore or delete.  Obtain it from
\fBs9s backup --list --long\fP.

.TP
.BI \-\-backup-dir= DIR
Informational: the base directory of the ClickHouse \fBbackups\fP disk.
Does not change where ClickHouse writes the backup (which is governed by
the ClickHouse server storage configuration), but is recorded in the
backup metadata.

.TP
.BI \-\-title= STRING
A short human-readable label stored with the backup.  Only
\fI[A-Za-z0-9_.-]\fP characters are allowed; spaces are replaced with
underscores and other characters are stripped.

.TP
.B \-\-wait
Block until the job finishes and print the job progress.

.TP
.B \-\-log
Stream job log messages to the terminal.

.TP
.BI \-\-recurrence= CRONTAB
When used with \fB--create-schedule\fP, sets the backup schedule in
standard crontab format (e.g. \fI"0 2 * * *"\fP for daily at 02:00).

.\"
.\" SCHEDULING
.\"
.SH SCHEDULED BACKUPS

Backups can be scheduled to run automatically using \fB--create-schedule\fP.
The \fB--recurrence\fP option uses standard crontab syntax.

.B Schedule a nightly full backup at 02:00
.nf
s9s backup \\
    --create-schedule \\
    --cluster-id=1 \\
    --nodes=192.168.1.10 \\
    --backup-method=clickhouse-native \\
    --backup-dir=/var/lib/clickhouse/backups/ \\
    --title=nightly_full \\
    --recurrence="0 2 * * *"
.fi

.B Schedule a 6-hourly incremental backup
.nf
s9s backup \\
    --create-schedule \\
    --cluster-id=1 \\
    --nodes=192.168.1.10 \\
    --backup-method=clickhouse-native-incr \\
    --backup-dir=/var/lib/clickhouse/backups/ \\
    --title=incr_6h \\
    --recurrence="0 */6 * * *"
.fi

.B List schedules
.nf
s9s backup --list-schedules --long --cluster-id=1
.fi

.\"
.\" NOTES
.\"
.SH NOTES

.IP \(bu 3
The \fBallow_non_empty_tables\fP setting is enabled during restore.  This
allows restoring into a database that already has tables and data \(em
ClickHouse replaces the table contents from the backup rather than
appending to them.

.IP \(bu 3
ClickHouse backup names are derived from the \fB--title\fP value.  Names
must contain only \fI[A-Za-z0-9_.-]\fP; invalid characters are stripped
automatically.  If the title is empty or produces an empty name, a
timestamp-based name is used (\fIbackup_YYYYmmddTHHMMSS\fP).

.IP \(bu 3
Credentials (\fBX-ClickHouse-User\fP / \fBX-ClickHouse-Key\fP headers)
must not contain CR or LF characters; cmon will reject such values.

